2026-04-16 12:10:15 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Input Cable (+) 6'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that the positive line is at ~11.99 V up to control module 5, and also present on the Input (+) terminal of module 6, but drops to 0 V at Output (+) 6 and all points downstream (module 7 etc.). Visual inspection revealed the only anomaly: the port n of Control Input Cable (+) 6 is disconnected (floating). This means the series 12 V path is interrupted at module 6’s positive input, so although the upstream side is energized, the internal connection that should route +12 V through module 6 to its output is open. This open connection prevents power from reaching control modules 6–8 and the load module, explaining why all control LEDs are missing and the lamp does not turn on despite all switches being ON. Repairing/reconnecting Control Input Cable (+) 6 at port n (or replacing that cable/terminal assembly) should restore continuity of the positive line and allow the load and downstream indicators to operate normally.'
